@startuml

actor "Warehouse Manager" as WM
participant "Screen" as UI
participant ":PriceListController" as PLC
participant ":IPriceListService" as PLS

WM -> UI : 1. Clicks "Edit" on a price list
activate UI
UI -> PLC : 2.1 GET /api/pricelist/GetById/{id}
activate PLC

PLC -> PLS : 2.2 GetByIdAsync(id)
activate PLS
PLS --> PLC
deactivate PLS

PLC --> UI : 2.3 Return existing data
deactivate PLC
UI -> UI : 2.4 Display form populated with data
deactivate UI

WM -> UI : 3 Clicks "Save Changes"
activate UI
UI -> PLC : 4.1 PUT /api/pricelist/Update/{id}(dto)
activate PLC

' Note: The code for Update in the controller might also re-fetch the entity first.
' This diagram simplifies it to a direct update call.
PLC -> PLS : 4.2 UpdateAsync(entity)
activate PLS
PLS --> PLC : 4.3 Confirmation
deactivate PLS

PLC --> UI : 4.4 Return success result
deactivate PLC
UI --> WM : 5 Display "Update successful" message
deactivate UI
@enduml